`closeEndpoints` is never a function, the code supports a situation where `closeEndpoints` is not passed in and the `cb` callback function is the first parameter. From the `node-usb` code:

```javascript
	if (typeof closeEndpoints == 'function') {
		cb = closeEndpoints;
		closeEndpoints = null;
	}
```

Hence why there are two definitions for `release()`:

```javascript
    release(closeEndpoints?: (err?: string) => void, cb?: (err?: string) => void): void;
    release(cb?: (err?: string) => void): void;
```

